description="Local LLM chat for your NAS CPU.\n\nFilamind AI runs large language models on your DS1821+'s AMD Ryzen V1500B (AVX2 + FMA), with full privacy — no data leaves your network. CPU-only build using the latest llama.cpp — supports Llama 3.x, Qwen 2.5, Gemma 2/3, Phi-3/4, Aya Expanse, DeepSeek, and Mixtral up to 70B parameters thanks to the 32GB+ RAM ceiling.\n\n• Built-in chat UI accessible from DSM (click the Filamind AI icon)\n• Pure CPU inference — no GPU needed\n• OpenAI-compatible HTTP API on port 8181 for use with other tools\n• Auto-discovers .gguf model files in /volume1/FilamindAI/models/, /volume1/AI/models/, or any custom path you configure\n• Multi-user with admin/user roles, full Arabic + English UI, optional cloud fallback to OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini\n• Runs as a native DSM package, fully managed via Package Center\n\nAfter installation:\n1. Place a GGUF model file in /volume1/FilamindAI/models/ (use File Station)\n2. Start the package — the chat will be available on port 8181\n3. Click the Filamind AI icon in DSM to open the web interface\n\nRecommended models: Llama 3.2 3B Q4 (fast, modern), Mistral 7B v0.3 Q4 (balanced), Aya Expanse 8B (excellent Arabic), Llama 3.3 70B Q4 (premium, slow on CPU).\n\nDeveloped by Abdelmonem Awad (eg2@live.com)."
description_enu="Filamind AI — local LLM chat for your DS1821+. Runs modern open-source models (Llama 3.x, Qwen 2.5, Gemma 2/3, Aya, DeepSeek, Mixtral, up to 70B) on the Ryzen V1500B's AVX2 CPU. No GPU needed. Built-in chat UI + OpenAI-compatible API on port 8181. Multi-user, Arabic+English. Developed by Abdelmonem Awad (eg2@live.com)."
